 At approximately 1:20 a.m., a shooting was reported at Winston-Salem State University in the area of Lot W near Wilson Hall and Gleason-Hairston Terrace. The campus was placed on lockdown at approximately 1:30 a.m. The lockdown was lifted at approximately 4:50 a.m. Traffic near the incident is restricted.

We can confirm that there has been one fatality and one injured individual. Both are believed to be students. The suspected gunman is not believed to be a current student. The campus has been cleared; the gunman has not been apprehended.

